File: Former President Jacob Zuma will have a lot to answer to at the Zondo Commission. JOHANNESBURG - Former President Jacob Zuma is set to testify at the Zondo Commission of Inquiry into state capture on Monday. That's after he was mentioned in statements and testimony from various witnesses. LIVESTREAM: Zuma appears at state capture inquiry He will appear at the Zondo Commission between 15-19 July. However, Zuma seems unfazed and in high spirits ahead of his appearance after he posted a video on Twitter on Sunday.  